    },
    {
      "id": 86,
      "title": "v3.6.1 [CRITICAL] Atomic _flush: write to temp file then rename — prevents corruption if crash during backup rotation",
      "description": "Overseer self-audit finding: _flush does backup rotation (bak→bak.2, current→bak, write new) with 3 separate writeFileSync calls. Crash between any two leaves data in inconsistent state. Fix: write new data to nexus.json.tmp, then rename .bak→.bak.2, current→.bak, tmp→current. Rename is atomic on most OS. server/db/store.ts _flush().",
      "status": "done",
      "priority": 2,
      "sort_order": 22,
      "linked_files": "[]",
      "created_at": "2026-04-10T07:30:39.715Z",
      "updated_at": "2026-04-10T07:33:34.228Z"
    },
    {
      "id": 87,
      "title": "v3.6.1 [CRITICAL] Add write mutex to _flush — prevent concurrent writeFileSync truncation",
      "description": "Overseer self-audit: two near-simultaneous _flush() calls could truncate nexus.json. Node is single-threaded but async operations (WebSocket broadcast → activity log → _flush) can interleave at await points. Fix: simple boolean lock on _flush, skip if already flushing. server/db/store.ts.",
      "status": "done",
      "priority": 2,
      "sort_order": 23,
      "linked_files": "[]",
      "created_at": "2026-04-10T07:30:43.005Z",
      "updated_at": "2026-04-10T07:33:34.248Z"
    },
    {
      "id": 88,
      "title": "v3.6.1 [IMPORTANT] Cap _semanticAutoLink promises — limit concurrent fire-and-forget embedding calls",
      "description": "Overseer self-audit: _semanticAutoLink is fire-and-forget async. High-volume decision recording could accumulate thousands of unawaited promises. Fix: track pending semantic link count, skip if >3 already in flight. server/db/store.ts.",
      "status": "done",
      "priority": 1,
      "sort_order": 24,
      "linked_files": "[]",
      "created_at": "2026-04-10T07:30:44.757Z",
      "updated_at": "2026-04-10T07:33:34.483Z"
    },
    {
      "id": 89,
      "title": "v3.6.1 [IMPORTANT] Batch embeddings cache writes — writeFileSync on every getEmbedding is I/O bottleneck",
      "description": "Overseer self-audit: server/lib/embeddings.ts saveCache() does writeFileSync on every new embedding. Fix: debounce — save at most once per 5 seconds via setTimeout, or on process exit. server/lib/embeddings.ts.",
      "status": "done",
      "priority": 1,
      "sort_order": 25,
      "linked_files": "[]",
      "created_at": "2026-04-10T07:30:47.015Z",
      "updated_at": "2026-04-10T07:33:34.965Z"
    },
    {
      "id": 90,
      "title": "v3.6.1 [IMPORTANT] Usage burn rate: sort history by timestamp before calculating — don't assume array order",
      "description": "Overseer self-audit: calculateBurnRates() assumes history[0] is newest. If store was manipulated or entries inserted out of order, rates are wrong. Fix: sort by created_at descending before calculating. server/routes/estimator.ts or usage.ts.",
      "status": "done",
      "priority": 1,
      "sort_order": 26,
      "linked_files": "[]",
      "created_at": "2026-04-10T07:30:50.310Z",
      "updated_at": "2026-04-10T07:33:35.447Z"
    },
    {
      "id": 91,
      "title": "v4.0 Phase 1: Refactor MCP server from HTTP proxy to self-contained with in-process NexusStore at ~/.nexus/nexus.json",
      "description": "The biggest v4.0 change. Currently server/mcp/index.ts proxies every tool call to localhost:3001 via HTTP. Refactor: import NexusStore directly into the MCP process, read/write ~/.nexus/nexus.json. All 20 tools work without Express running. LM Studio calls optional (graceful degradation). GPU signal + AI semaphore still apply for AI features.",
      "status": "done",
      "priority": 2,
      "sort_order": 22,
      "linked_files": "[]",
      "created_at": "2026-04-10T09:20:33.352Z",
      "updated_at": "2026-04-10T09:27:12.353Z"
    },
    {
      "id": 92,
      "title": "v4.0 Phase 2: Build Claude Code Plugin package (.claude-plugin/plugin.json, .mcp.json, skills/, agents/, hooks.json)",
      "description": "Create plugin directory structure: plugin.json metadata, .mcp.json pointing to bundled server, 4 skills (brief/plan/audit/status as SKILL.md), Overseer agent as AGENT.md, hooks.json for SessionStart+Stop. Bundle MCP server with esbuild.",
      "status": "done",
      "priority": 2,
      "sort_order": 23,
      "linked_files": "[]",
      "created_at": "2026-04-10T09:20:35.269Z",
      "updated_at": "2026-04-10T09:38:18.764Z"
    },
    {
      "id": 93,
      "title": "v4.0 Phase 3: Create kronosderet/nexus-marketplace GitHub repo with marketplace.json",
      "description": "Self-hosted marketplace — no approval needed, immediately available. Users install via /plugin marketplace add kronosderet/nexus-marketplace then /plugin install nexus@nexus-marketplace. marketplace.json lists the Nexus plugin with source pointing to the plugin directory.",
      "status": "backlog",
      "priority": 1,
      "sort_order": 24,
      "linked_files": "[]",
      "created_at": "2026-04-10T09:20:37.366Z",
      "updated_at": "2026-04-10T09:20:37.366Z"
    },
    {
      "id": 94,
      "title": "v4.0 Phase 4: Submit to official directories — tool annotations, privacy policy, 3+ examples, icon, LICENSE",
      "description": "Submit to both: Claude Code Plugin Directory (https://clau.de/plugin-directory-submission) and Anthropic MCPB Directory (https://forms.gle/tyiAZvch1kDADKoP9). Requirements: readOnlyHint/destructiveHint on every tool, privacy policy in README + manifest, 3+ working examples with prompts + expected outputs, LICENSE file, 512x512 icon, works on macOS + Windows clean environments.",
      "status": "backlog",
      "priority": 1,
      "sort_order": 25,
      "linked_files": "[]",
      "created_at": "2026-04-10T09:20:40.312Z",
      "updated_at": "2026-04-10T09:20:40.312Z"
    },
    {
      "id": 95,
      "title": "v4.0 Phase 5: Decouple Express dashboard — reads ~/.nexus/nexus.json, installable separately as optional visualization",
      "description": "The React dashboard becomes optional. Express server reads the same ~/.nexus/nexus.json that the plugin writes. Not part of the plugin — purely visualization. Can be installed via npm install -g nexus-dashboard or via nexus-dev.bat.",
      "status": "backlog",
      "priority": 0,
      "sort_order": 26,
      "linked_files": "[]",
      "created_at": "2026-04-10T09:20:41.372Z",
      "updated_at": "2026-04-10T09:20:41.372Z"
    },
    {
      "id": 96,
      "title": "v4.0 Pre-release: Replace 17 hardcoded C:/Projects paths with configurable NEXUS_PROJECTS_DIR env var across 12 server files",
      "description": "Pre-release audit found C:/Projects hardcoded in: actions.ts, focus.ts, github.ts, init.ts, overseer.ts (3x), predict.ts, pulse.ts, remediate.ts (3x), scratchpad.ts, terminal.ts (2x), fileWatcher.ts, overseerPoller.ts, cli/nexus.js. All need process.env.NEXUS_PROJECTS_DIR || homedir() fallback. Critical for plugin distribution — other users don't have C:/Projects.",
      "status": "done",
      "priority": 2,
      "sort_order": 27,
      "linked_files": "[]",
      "created_at": "2026-04-10T09:41:15.301Z",
      "updated_at": "2026-04-10T10:52:30.939Z"
    },
    {
      "id": 97,
      "title": "v4.1 [CMD-1] Always show session stats counters (done/review/active) even at 0 + show priority badges on task cards",
      "description": "Now panel: session stats grid only renders when doneToday > 0 || review > 0 — vanishes on fresh day. Always show (0 is valid data). Kanban: task.priority (0/1/2) exists in data but never displayed. Add color-coded priority dot or badge on TaskCard. Remove dead Fuel+Zap imports.",
