    {
      "id": 66,
      "project": "Nexus",
      "summary": "GPU-aware abort signal replaces all fixed AI inference timeouts. Created shared server/lib/gpuSignal.ts that monitors nvidia-smi every 15s: as long as GPU util > 30% or power > 50W, the request stays alive. Only aborts when GPU idle for 60s (inference finished/failed) or after 1h absolute max. This solves the fundamental problem: local AI inference time depends on context × offload × model size (30s to 40+ minutes), so no fixed timeout works. Applied to overseer.ts ask() and autoSummary.ts askAI(). Also added /api/overseer/code-audit endpoint that reads the full codebase and sends to local AI, and bumped Express body limit to 2MB.",
      "decisions": [
        "GPU utilization + power draw is the signal for AI inference liveness, not wall-clock time. The GPU IS the sensor.",
        "Shared utility in server/lib/gpuSignal.ts — used by overseer and autoSummary, extensible to any future AI endpoint",
        "Idle threshold 60s (4 consecutive idle readings), absolute max 1 hour. nvidia-smi failures treated as 'active' to avoid killing on transient errors.",
        "Express body limit bumped to 2MB to support large code-audit payloads sent via /ask/start"
      ],
      "blockers": [],
      "files_touched": [
        "server/lib/gpuSignal.ts",
        "server/routes/overseer.ts",
