    {
      "id": 77,
      "project": "Nexus",
      "summary": "v3.7: Frontend restructure — 10 modules merged to 7. Command module (Compass + Missions merged into strategic/kanban tabs), Log module (Activity + Sessions merged into activity/sessions tabs), Bookmarks removed from module registry. Bundle size dropped 338KB → 327KB despite more features. Both new modules share data + search/filter infrastructure. Strategic view keeps Now/Next/Later/Done panels with thoughts + AI plan + critique. Kanban view keeps drag-drop + task creation + status dots. Log view keeps type-filtered activity stream + project-filtered session list.",
      "decisions": [
        "Command module unifies Compass + Missions via tab toggle — same data, two visualizations. Strategic (read, plan, think) vs Kanban (create, move, delete). User picks the mode they need.",
        "Log module unifies Activity + Sessions via tab toggle — shared search input, sort order, and filter bar. Each tab shows its own filter chips (type for activity, project for sessions).",
        "Bookmarks removed from sidebar modules. The feature still exists via CLI/API but doesn't need a full dashboard page. Can be re-added as a sidebar widget later.",
        "Module count 10 → 7: Command, Dashboard (Pulse), Fuel, Graph, Overseer, Log, Terminal. Cleaner navigation, less cognitive load, no functional overlap."
      ],
