    {
      "id": 81,
      "project": "Nexus",
      "summary": "v4.0 strategic plan complete. Nexus becomes an official Claude Code extension via two channels: Plugin (GitHub marketplace, /plugin install) and MCPB (Anthropic Directory). Five phases planned: (1) self-contained MCP server with in-process NexusStore at ~/.nexus/, (2) plugin package with skills/agents/hooks, (3) self-hosted marketplace on GitHub, (4) official directory submissions with tool annotations + privacy policy + examples, (5) decoupled optional dashboard. Also completed: v3.7 frontend restructure (10→7 modules), v3.6.1 self-audit fixes, successful 46k-token code audit by local Overseer, GPU signal tuning (removed absolute timeout, lowered idle thresholds), AI semaphore for slot contention, aiFetch via undici for no headers timeout.",
      "decisions": [
        "Two distribution channels: Claude Code Plugin (self-hosted marketplace, immediate) + MCPB (Anthropic Directory, review required)",
        "Self-contained MCP is the gating architecture change — store embedded in MCP process, not HTTP proxy to Express",
        "Data location moves to ~/.nexus/nexus.json (standard user config dir, not project-specific)",
        "LM Studio is optional enhancer — AI features gracefully degrade, core tools always work",
        "Dashboard becomes optional visualization layer reading the same data file"
      ],
      "blockers": [],
      "files_touched": [],
      "tags": [
        "v4.0",
        "strategy",
        "plugin",
        "marketplace",
        "mcpb",
        "extension",
        "architecture"
      ],
      "created_at": "2026-04-10T09:20:50.004Z"
    },
    {
      "id": 82,
      "project": "Nexus",
      "summary": "v4.0 Phase 1 shipped: self-contained MCP server. Created server/mcp/localApi.ts — a local API adapter that routes MCP tool calls directly to NexusStore in-process (no Express HTTP proxy needed). Data stored at ~/.nexus/nexus.json (auto-created). MCP index.ts switches between standalone mode (NEXUS_STANDALONE=1 → localApi) and proxy mode (default → HTTP to localhost:3001). All core tools work standalone: tasks, decisions, thoughts, guard, critique, estimator, usage, sessions, activity, search, bookmarks, impact. AI features (Overseer, plan, code-audit) gracefully return 'AI unavailable' without LM Studio. Standalone test passes all checks. 153 Vitest tests pass.",
      "decisions": [
        "Adapter pattern: localApi.ts mimics the HTTP API interface but calls store methods directly — zero changes needed in tool handlers, only the transport layer switches",
        "Data at ~/.nexus/nexus.json (standard user config dir) — auto-creates directory on first run",
        "NEXUS_STANDALONE=1 env var toggles mode — MCP server supports both standalone and proxy in the same codebase",
        "AI features degrade to error messages, not crashes — the plugin works without LM Studio for all non-AI tools"
      ],
