    {
      "id": 66,
      "decision": "Resonance architecture: Intent->Force->Physics 3-layer pipeline. IntentSystem evaluates priority-ordered per-type evaluators (8 intents). ForceRegistry accumulates field/hex/flee forces. PhysicsLayer integrates with terrain drag and speed caps. Harmony field drives formations — no springs, squads inject at slot positions creating peaks units drift toward.",
      "context": "",
      "project": "resonance godot",
      "alternatives": [],
      "tags": [],
      "created_at": "2026-04-06T22:08:12.540Z"
    },
    {
      "id": 67,
      "decision": "Resonance tech stack: Godot 4.6.1, Forward+ renderer, GDScript, GLSL compute shaders (GPU Navier-Stokes fluid sim for 7-tone harmony field), zero external assets — all visuals via _draw() polar equations. RTX 3070 Ti target. Ported from Python/Pygame 38K LOC.",
      "context": "",
      "project": "resonance godot",
      "alternatives": [],
      "tags": [],
      "created_at": "2026-04-06T22:08:22.995Z"
    },
    {
      "id": 68,
      "decision": "Resonance design philosophy: All game constants are base-7 derived (7,14,21,42,49,77,98,147,196,245,343,490). GF(7) Galois field arithmetic governs combat multipliers, tone interactions, terrain CA. Harmony is everything — every system reads harmony. No sprites, no assets, pure math visualization.",
      "context": "",
      "project": "resonance godot",
      "alternatives": [],
      "tags": [],
      "created_at": "2026-04-06T22:08:28.609Z"
    },
