      "recommendation": "## PLAN\nFocus on stabilizing the core gameplay loop by fixing critical hex effect triggers and ensuring CPU/GPU parity for field gradients.\n\n## TASKS\n1. [20m] Hex system: wire active_hexes to units — ensures ForceRegistry effects (void, lethargy, etc.) actually apply to entities.\n2. [30m] CPU fallback sample_gradient tone-0 fix — prevents visual/logic breakage on non-GPU hardware by aligning harmony_field.gd with GPU behavior.\n3. [15m] Noosphere: Debug and test compute shader pipeline — verifies the RenderingDevice dispatch is stable before moving to visualization tasks.\n\n## RATIONALE\nThe total estimated time (65m) respects your 79m runway while leaving a buffer for the 25 uncommitted changes. I prioritized fixing the Hex system first because it is a functional blocker for combat logic, followed by technical parity and pipeline verification to prevent future debugging loops.\n\n## AVOID\n- Noosphere: Field visualization — defer until the underlying compute shader dispatch is verified as stable.\n- AUDIT tasks — these are low priority compared to active system breakage in the hex/gradient logic.",
