      "id": 8,
      "created_at": "2026-04-07T22:46:01.157Z",
      "source": "ask",
      "question": "Given the v3.3 audit tier A tasks #111-#117 (version sync, CLI+MCPB tool list stale at 6/18, WebSocket infinite reconnect bug, server hardening trio, Compass NaN guards, onboard version) and a 5% weekly fuel constraint: which 2-3 should ship FIRST next session, ranked by user-visible impact divided by implementation risk? Be specific — name tasks by number and give one-line rationale each.",
      "recommendation": "### SITUATION\nThe workspace is in a critical \"v3.3 Patch\" state. A recent audit has identified high-severity technical debt and stability risks across **Nexus**. While progress is high (78 completed), the 5% weekly fuel constraint necessitates extreme surgical precision to avoid system instability or network exhaustion.\n\n### PRIORITIES\nRanked by Impact/Risk ratio:\n\n1.  **v3.3 [TIER-A] WebSocket exponential backoff**: Highest priority; prevents \"reconnect storms\" that could crash your server or exhaust remaining weekly fuel during outages.\n2.  **v3.3 [TIER-A] Update CLI 'nexus mcp' help & mcpb/README.md**: High impact, extremely low risk; fixes the dangerous documentation gap (6 vs 18 tools) that currently misleads users/installers.\n3.  **v3.3 [TIER-A] Server hardening (deleteScratchpad _flush + unsafe Object.assign)**: Critical for data integrity; prevents silent data loss and memory-unsafe operations in the core Nexus engine.\n\n### RISKS\n*   **Resource Exhaustion**: With only 5% weekly fuel remaining, attempting \"Tier B\" or \"Tier C\" tasks will lead to session failure/starvation.\n*   **Documentation Drift**: The discrepancy between actual tools (18) and listed tools (6) is a high-risk blocker for any new project onboarding.\n*   **Uncommitted Work**: `Nexus`, `Noosphere`, and `Firewall-Godot` all have uncommitted changes; a sudden fuel depletion risks losing the current audit context.\n\n### RECOMMENDATIONS\n1.  **Execute Tier A \"Stability Trio\" only**: Focus exclusively on WebSocket backoff, tool list updates, and server hardening. \n2.  **Defer All Tier B/C Tasks**: Do not touch accessibility or refactoring until next week's fuel replenishment.\n3.  **Commit Immediately**: Commit the current `Nexus` changes before the session ends to protect the audit findings.",
      "recommendation_hash": "### situation the workspace is in a critical \"v3.3 patch\" state. a recent audit has identified high-",
      "context_snapshot": {
