      "recommendation": "### SITUATION\nThe Nexus ecosystem has achieved \"self-protecting\" status with v3.5, but structural intelligence is still maturing. While the metabrain can now monitor hardware (GPU-aware signals) and automate logging, it lacks deep semantic reasoning and high-fidelity context injection. You have significant uncommitted work across all core repos and a growing \"blind spot\" in **Noosphere**.\n\n### PRIORITIES\n1.  **Semantic Knowledge Graph Enrichment (High Impact):** Move beyond keyword overlap for auto-linking. Implement vector-based or LLM-driven semantic linking to resolve the 12 orphan decisions and bridge the gap between disparate project modules.\n2.  **End-to-End Audit Validation (Critical Risk):** The recently shipped code-audit feature is unverified. You must run a full-cycle audit on **Firewall-Godot** or **Shadowrun** to ensure the \"metabrain auditing itself\" loop is closed and functional.\n3.  **Context Enrichment (SessionStart/Brief):** Upgrade the `SessionStart` hook to inject structured project state (current sprint, active blockers, recent git diffs) rather than just basic identifiers. This reduces the \"cold start\" cognitive load for Claude Code.\n4.  **Noosphere Indexing (Visibility):** Address the blind spot. Establish a decision-logging baseline for **Noosphere** to ensure it doesn't become a disconnected silo in the Knowledge Graph.\n\n### RISKS\n*   **Unverified Automation:** Relying on unvetted audit features creates a false sense of security regarding technical debt.\n*   **Knowledge Fragmentation:** The 12 orphan decisions and semantic linking gap will lead to an increasingly fragmented and \"hallucinatory\" Knowledge Graph as the project scales.\n*   **Uncommitted Work:** All major repos (**Nexus**, **Firewall-Godot**, **Noosphere**) have uncommitted changes, risking loss of recent architectural refinements.\n\n### RECOMMENDATIONS\n1.  **Execute a \"Verification Sprint\":** Run a manual audit using the new v3.5 tools on a secondary project to validate the audit pipeline.\n2.  **Implement Semantic Linker:** Integrate an embedding-based approach for the Knowledge Graph to resolve orphan decisions.\n3.  **Commit & Sync:** Resolve all uncommitted changes across the fleet before initiating v3.6 development.",
